 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;tr>
 &lt;td>description&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: center">string&lt;/td>
 &lt;td style="text-align: center">true&lt;/td>
 &lt;td>Description of the tool that is passed to the LLM.&lt;/td>
 &lt;/tr>
 &lt;/tbody>
&lt;/table></description></item><item><title>firestore-get-documents</title><link>https://xgs925.github.io/genai-toolbox/v1.0.6/resources/tools/firestore/firestore-get-documents/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://xgs925.github.io/genai-toolbox/v1.0.6/resources/tools/firestore/firestore-get-documents/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about">About&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>A &lt;code>firestore-get-documents&lt;/code> tool retrieves multiple documents from Firestore by
their paths.
It&amp;rsquo;s compatible with the following sources:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://xgs925.github.io/genai-toolbox/v1.0.6/resources/sources/firestore/">firestore&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;code>firestore-get-documents&lt;/code> takes one input parameter &lt;code>documentPaths&lt;/code> which is an
array of document paths, and returns the documents&amp;rsquo; data along with metadata
such as existence status, creation time, update time, and read time.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="example">Example&lt;/h2>
